(726, 1, '2012-10-06 18:44:33', '2012-10-06 18:44:33', 'This is my favourite project I have worked on so far.  My client''s work was so beautiful it really wasn''t difficult getting the inspiration for the design.  I quickly identified the purpose of the website - to showcase David''s photography and advertise his workshops.  From there it was simple, make the images stand out.  They done this on their own, so I just had to make everything else fade slightly into the background, only being seen when necessary, and not cluttering up the page.\n\nThis website was wholly built in Wordpress which means David can update each and every page, and add new photos to the site when he choses.  It also has comment functionality and the ability to share links to his photos on facebook and twitter.  The e-commerce side of the website means that customers can buy prints from David easily through paypal.', 'Photography E-Commerce Website', '', 'draft', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'photography-e-commerce-site', '', '', '2018-03-15 18:05:53', '2018-03-15 18:05:53', '', 0, 'http://huddersfieldwebsitedesigner.co.uk/?post_type=websites&#038;p=81', 3, 'website', '', 0),
(727, 1, '2012-10-06 20:01:48', '2012-10-06 20:01:48', 'This Cleckheaton Tiling Website started off from scratch, with no logo or even company name!  A logo was first thing this client needed.  He wanted to adapt it to fit business cards along with a website.  We discussed the kind of website he was looking for, and identified that he was wanting to aim himself quite upmarket.  This then led me to the logo design which is simply his name and the word ''tiling''.  We chose this because it would be easy for people to remember as a url, and it described what he was doing perfectly.\r\n\r\nI chose a classical font to imbue a feeling of quality.  I iterated how important it was that someone landing on the site knew exactly was the site was selling, with this in mind, I chose bathroom tiles as a backdrop.', 'Cleckheaton Tiling Website', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'huddersfield-cleckheaton-tiling-website', '', '', '2018-03-15 17:40:26', '2018-03-15 17:40:26', '', 0, 'http://huddersfieldwebsitedesigner.co.uk/?post_type=websites&#038;p=87', 2, 'website', '', 0),
(728, 1, '2013-01-05 20:04:13', '2013-01-05 20:04:13', 'PLG Engineering of Mirfield, Huddersfield contacted me asking me whether I could create them a brochure website advertising what they did.  They found that people had been looking for them online and when they didn''t find them, were a bit unsure of them, or whether or not they existed.  They wanted this website to give themselves an online presence.  They already had a logo so I took the colours from that logo and used them in the design of the site.  The colours being red and yellow worked very well since they were a heating engineering company, so when you went on the site, you immediately had a feeling of warmth.\r\n\r\nThey didn''t need many pages, just enough to show their products, who they were and how to get in touch with them.  They were very pleased with the end product, liking how clear it was to see who they were and what they did.', 'Mirfield Heating Engineering Company', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'a-mirfield-websit-engineering-company', '', '', '2018-03-16 10:14:06', '2018-03-16 10:14:06', '', 0, 'http://huddersfieldwebsitedesigner.co.uk/?post_type=websites&#038;p=96', 22, 'website', '', 0),
(729, 1, '2012-04-05 21:20:53', '2012-04-05 21:20:53', 'This project was a simple redesign of the existing site.  Huddersfield Driving School already had a website.  They wanted some social icons adding such as facebook like button, and twitter share button.  They also required a feed from their facebook page, which meant whenever they made a new post on their facebook page, it would come through onto their website.\r\n\r\nThe site was integrated with paypal, enabling visitors to the site to buy driving lessons over the internet with their paypal account.\r\n\r\nWe also decided to go for a redesign as well to make it brighter and more inviting to users.  The original html and content was kept exactly the same and extra content such as the recently passed carousel was added to the top of the page.', 'Huddersfield Driving School', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'huddersfield-driving-school', '', '', '2018-03-15 18:24:21', '2018-03-15 18:24:21', '', 0, 'http://huddersfieldwebsitedesigner.co.uk/?post_type=websites&#038;p=342', 23, 'website', '', 1),
(730, 1, '2013-04-22 16:53:38', '2013-04-22 16:53:38', '<p>Branscombe Holiday Let approached me for a revamp of their existing website, and a logo design.  The owner was unable to update it herself, and wanted to give it a fresh look and add some social links.  I also optimised the website for search engines such as google and yahoo.</p>\n<p>I created a design reminiscent of the sea-side to reflect the aim of the website - to advertise holiday accommodation by the sea.  I used blues and creams to give the site a neutral, warm, unassuming feel, whilst making sure it was uncluttered and clear to navigate.</p>\n<p>The website has been designed and built using Wordpress.  This means my client can now edit the website herself, adding new images and text to any page.</p>', 'Holiday Let Website', '', 'draft', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'holiday-let-website', '', '', '2018-03-15 18:06:46', '2018-03-15 18:06:46', '', 0, 'http://huddersfieldwebsitedesigner.co.uk/?post_type=websites&#038;p=354', 13, 'website', '', 0),
